{#
  Template: ng-module-to-nextjs-feature.jinja2
  Mapping:  MAP-006
  Source:   Angular 2 NgModule (*.module.ts)
  Target:   Next.js feature folder index + barrel exports

  Key translation rules:
    @NgModule({ declarations: [FooComponent] }) → FooComponent.tsx in feature folder
    @NgModule({ imports: [RouterModule] })       → next/navigation imports in components
    @NgModule({ providers: [FooService] })       → src/services/foo/ module
    @NgModule({ exports: [FooComponent] })       → export default / named export in .tsx
    SharedModule imports                         → import from src/components/shared/
    CommonModule                                 → built-in React (no import needed)
    FormsModule / ReactiveFormsModule           → React controlled components / Zod validation
    HttpClientModule                            → fetch() API (no module needed)
    RouterModule.forChild(routes)               → Next.js App Router file-based routing

  Output structure for a feature module:
    frontend/src/components/{feature_name}/
      ├── index.ts                  ← barrel exports (replaces @NgModule exports)
      ├── {FeatureName}Component.tsx
      ├── {FeatureName}Component.test.tsx
      └── types.ts                  ← (optional) feature-specific types
#}
